Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.92,0:07:45.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Girls, girls, come on, let's sit inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.60,0:08:02.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's sit inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.96,0:08:29.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, Mr. Perfect Form.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.51,0:08:32.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No, no, I don't. You've got to... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.47,0:08:33.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Look. What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:35.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to snap your wrist on the backhand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.84,0:08:38.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Usually I like a little music at this point, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.76,0:08:40.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, I want to play in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.81,0:08:43.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, all right, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:44.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to snap your wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.69,0:08:45.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.44,0:08:49.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, we should stop doing this for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.73,0:08:53.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Doing... Doing what? We're not doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.11,0:08:54.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah, I know that. - Yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.95,0:08:57.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. No, fine, fine. Maybe you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.12,0:08:59.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Does your wife mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:01.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my wife doesn't even know you exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.95,0:09:03.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,which, most certainly, is for the best, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:05.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.54,0:09:09.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,God, you know, Lori, you know why you have to ask that question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.25,0:09:10.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- 'Cause you've never been married. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:12.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is marriage synonymous with deception?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.38,0:09:13.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.80,0:09:16.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that, you know, when two people...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.26,0:09:18.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,When two people get married
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.93,0:09:21.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and they live together for a long time, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.68,0:09:26.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I like hanging out with you, you know, so sue me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:31.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're funny, and you're cute, and, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.15,0:09:34.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We talk about the courts and which judge is senile
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:37.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and which one wears a gun under his robe and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.28,0:09:38.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God. You know, Lori,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.07,0:09:42.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,another time, another place, and who knows, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.20,0:09:45.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.33,0:09:46.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's a light docket.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.67,0:09:48.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no, I won two out of three.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.21,0:09:49.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make it the best out of five.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:52.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, well, that's good, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.96,0:09:54.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because today I let you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:56.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.68,0:09:57.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- See you. - Sure you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:04.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.68,0:10:06.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Free as a bird, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.02,0:10:08.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You go everywhere you want with whomever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.85,0:10:10.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That much freedom could maybe get a fellow into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.48,0:10:11.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.56,0:10:12.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like my keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.94,0:10:15.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be you don't remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:16.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, sure, I remember you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.78,0:10:18.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You were at the movie house the other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.11,0:10:20.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm disappointed. I'm hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:22.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like my keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:25.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Max Cady.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.66,0:10:28.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You look the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.29,0:10:30.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe 15 pounds heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.33,0:10:31.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But they say the average man
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.67,0:10:34.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,gains a pound a year till he's about...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.17,0:10:35.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:39.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Gains a pound a year till he's about 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.97,0:10:43.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Me? I dropped a pound every year of my sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.43,0:10:47.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Atlanta, '77. - You got it. July.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.81,0:10:51.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourteen years since I held a set of keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.61,0:10:56.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you look good, healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.07,0:11:00.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you. 'Cause it's a struggle to stay healthy in the joint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.74,0:11:02.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But you wouldn't know about that, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.07,0:11:04.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were me, they would stick you with the white trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.87,0:11:06.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't strike a lick of work all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.50,0:11:11.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, this little old cigar is my only vice
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:15.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,'cause I needed a vice in the joint to remind me I was human.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.46,0:11:18.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what brings you to New Essex?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.92,0:11:20.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:23.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, the South.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.55,0:11:27.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking of settling right down here in New Essex, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.60,0:11:29.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been following me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.77,0:11:31.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a small town. Everywhere you turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.19,0:11:32.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess, we're gonna run into each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.81,0:11:34.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, take care, Mr. Cady.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.19,0:11:35.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:40.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna learn about loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.57,0:11:41.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.12,0:11:53.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, could you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.17,0:11:55.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.79,0:11:57.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:12:00.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- What're you working on? - It's English.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:03.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We're supposed to read Look Homeward, Angel,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:05.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,which is a kind of reminiscence,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.14,0:12:07.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and we have to attempt something in the same style.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.97,0:12:12.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's it about, your reminiscence?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.23,0:12:14.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The houseboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:18.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the houseboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.99,0:12:25.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not even July 3rd yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.41,0:12:26.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.49,0:12:27.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I was thinking we ought to take
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.87,0:12:29.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,two weeks off and go up to Wilmington
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.20,0:12:30.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,like the old times, dock the houseboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.79,0:12:32.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to in early June.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:34.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember you said you didn't have time this summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.25,0:12:35.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I probably don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:36.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, now I don't, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.88,0:12:39.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, Dani's got summer school till Labor Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.42,0:12:40.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that critical
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.92,0:12:43.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that she can't miss two damn weeks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:45.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, the alternative was to expel her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.51,0:12:48.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, maybe this Drama teacher from the college
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.85,0:12:50.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,will get her excited about something, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.81,0:12:52.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, about him, probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:55.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, why'd they have to make such a stink,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.10,0:12:57.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,like she was on heroin, or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.36,0:12:59.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, marijuana, what's marijuana?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:01.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I smoked a little dope in our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.65,0:13:02.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:04.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, in some cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.15,0:13:05.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,it's considered almost a sacrament.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.86,0:13:07.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I realize in ours, it's forbidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:13.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Right up there with incest and necrophilia and bestiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:14.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Honey. Honey. Honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:16.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Worship of idols, cannibalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.83,0:13:17.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.54,0:13:19.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.79,0:13:21.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.78,0:15:15.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Sam. Sam, somebody's out there! - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.54,0:15:18.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, leave the light off. Leave it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.29,0:15:24.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him when the fireworks went off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.50,0:15:26.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.09,0:15:28.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- I think I talked to him this afternoon. - You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.68,0:15:33.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you the hell off my property!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.19,0:15:47.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.32,0:15:56.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I'm gonna make you think about loss."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.91,0:16:00.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Or, "I'm gonna make you learn about loss." Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:02.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's very poetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.25,0:16:04.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who is he? Where did he come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:05.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's from...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:09.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Leigh, get the dog off. Ben, get down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.76,0:16:12.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't mind me at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.63,0:16:14.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leigh, he's your dog. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:16.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he shouldn't be up on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:19.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna have dog hairs in the tea and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.27,0:16:21.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get down. So where's he from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:23.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he's from the hills, Pentecostal crackers, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.36,0:16:27.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What was he in prison for?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:30.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.57,0:16:32.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- You think it was battery? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:33.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, well, who did he batter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.57,0:16:35.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he batter a man? Did he batter a woman? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.91,0:16:36.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.08,0:16:40.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 14 years ago. You know, it's kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.91,0:16:42.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.00,0:16:46.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What does he want with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.88,0:16:49.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's just trying to bug us, just messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.75,0:16:52.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, he's an ex-con, so he's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:56.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, he's probably upset at the lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:16:58.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, your clientele.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.76,0:16:59.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:04.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Bye, Dad. - Bye, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.94,0:17:05.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You look tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.06,0:17:08.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. I needed that. Leigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.94,0:17:10.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leigh, I don't want to alarm her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.15,0:17:12.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but I'd rather Dani didn't wander out alone
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:14.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,on her soul-searching walks in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:15.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,at least till I've started a few things,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.78,0:17:17.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe even talked to the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:18.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she takes Benjamin with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:20.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Big Ben, our guard dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.58,0:17:22.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he gonna do, lick him to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.54,0:17:24.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Just tell her. - Tell her what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:25.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I hardly know anything about the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.00,0:17:27.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean his biography.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.58,0:17:28.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just there's some creep around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.00,0:17:31.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you see him again, call the cops and then call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.59,0:17:33.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What about a weapon, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:36.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In case things get exciting around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:38.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Leigh, would you really feel more secure
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:40.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with a loaded gun in the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.51,0:17:42.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd probably end up using it on each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.93,0:17:44.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Or Dani would.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.48,0:17:46.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not gonna do anything. He just got out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:49.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't want to go right back. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.90,0:17:55.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lee is a colorful character,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.49,0:17:57.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's still the best criminal lawyer in the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.82,0:17:59.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good. - Bonnie, get me Lee Heller.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:02.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, you defended this guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.83,0:18:03.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.87,0:18:05.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what makes you think he wants to harm you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:07.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday I was getting in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:10.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy comes up, we have a little conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.71,0:18:13.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He says to me, "You're gonna learn about loss."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:18.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd hardly qualify under the terrorist threat statutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:21.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, Tom, for Christ's sake, the guy's an ex-con.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.39,0:18:24.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know as well as I do what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.47,0:18:27.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, last night, there he was, he was behind our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.44,0:18:28.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah. Attempted B and E.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:30.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.35,0:18:33.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he was sitting on a wall that bounds our property.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.07,0:18:36.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even trespassing, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.86,0:18:38.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, come on. What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.57,0:18:40.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, get a restraining order.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.24,0:18:43.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I did. I filed one this morning. The hearing's in 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.66,0:18:47.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Good. I mean, you know, anything I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:49.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom, 14 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.71,0:18:54.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in this case I had a report on the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:18:56.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- It was a rape case. - That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:58.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Rape and aggravated sexual battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.72,0:19:00.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I had a report on this victim
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.55,0:19:03.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it came back that she was promiscuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.60,0:19:06.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.89,0:19:09.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I buried it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.73,0:19:11.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Whew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.02,0:19:15.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Anybody else know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.19,0:19:16.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, I buried it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.40,0:19:17.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I didn't show it to the client,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:19.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't show it to the prosecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.90,0:19:22.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you had seen what this guy had done to this girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:26.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"In every criminal prosecution, the accused shall have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.12,0:19:27.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"the Assistance of Counsel for his defense."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:29.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the Sixth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.33,0:19:30.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe in the Sixth Amendment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:33.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, that's why I left the Public Defender's Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.38,0:19:36.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no way to serve the law in that capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.25,0:19:37.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Some folks just don't have the right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:38.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to the best defense, huh, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:40.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Of course they deserve the best defense!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.76,0:19:43.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I mean, if you had seen what he did to this girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.55,0:19:44.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You buried the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:46.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, if it was your own daughter, Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:49.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah, I mean... - Buried the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.81,0:19:51.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:54.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:20:01.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't see how he could know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:02.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, he was illiterate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.20,0:20:04.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I had to read everything to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.74,0:20:06.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the probable cause affidavit,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.24,0:20:08.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the arrest reports, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.29,0:20:12.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he could know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.93,0:20:28.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dani, it's so quiet out here, and the light's so perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.14,0:20:31.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,why don't you get your book and come out here and read?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.39,0:20:32.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:34.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you why.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.48,0:20:39.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, is it because he's like a flasher or just a peeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:42.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know about that? A flasher?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.28,0:20:45.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you don't think I've been flashed before?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.32,0:20:47.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well, I certainly didn't mean to insult you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.49,0:20:49.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've been flashed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.33,0:20:52.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, if you want to come out, come on out. If you don't, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.50,0:20:54.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.33,0:20:57.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but don't go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.13,0:21:04.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Afternoon, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.85,0:21:10.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, Mr. Cady?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.15,0:21:21.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They're great at that age, ain't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.69,0:21:24.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All those discoveries ahead of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.24,0:21:25.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.11,0:21:28.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My own daughter, she don't even know me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.24,0:21:32.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,After I went inside, her mama told her I was dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.20,0:21:34.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,which, in a way, I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.62,0:21:38.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Mr. Cady, I realize that you suffered.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.84,0:21:42.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I understand your problem, but, I mean, why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:46.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I was your lawyer. I defended you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.93,0:21:49.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, why not badger the D.A. Or the judge?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.89,0:21:50.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"Badger."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.06,0:21:52.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Why not them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.77,0:21:55.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. Why not them? - "Badger."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.10,0:21:59.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Best I remember, they was just doing right by their jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.19,0:22:01.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I didn't do my job? Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.44,0:22:05.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I pleaded you out to a lesser occluded offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.57,0:22:07.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You could've gotten rape instead of battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:10.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'd have been up for parole either way in seven years
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.24,0:22:11.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,according to the Georgia penal code.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.53,0:22:12.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Rape is a capital offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.62,0:22:15.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you could've gotten life, you could've done death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.25,0:22:18.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You could be sitting on death row right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.92,0:22:22.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned to read during my stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.09,0:22:26.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,First, Spot Goes to the Farm,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.76,0:22:30.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,then Runaway Bunny, then law books, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.10,0:22:34.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that after I discharged you,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.27,0:22:36.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I acted as my own attorney?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.68,0:22:38.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Applied several times for an appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.77,0:22:40.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.11,0:22:43.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.44,0:22:45.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, here we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.61,0:22:49.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,two lawyers, for all practical purposes, talking shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.78,0:22:52.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. How much do you want, Mr. Cady?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:54.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How much do I want what?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.95,0:22:57.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How much money do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.41,0:23:01.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Money? Counselor, do I look destitute to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.08,0:23:04.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm open to discussion, within reasonable limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.09,0:23:08.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You ever been a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.59,0:23:09.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A what?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.72,0:23:10.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.47,0:23:15.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Some fat, hairy, ugly hillbilly's wet dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.06,0:23:21.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I realize that you suffered in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.27,0:23:22.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Suffered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.40,0:23:23.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- There's no question about that. - "Suffered."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.77,0:23:26.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know what suffering is, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.36,0:23:29.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Like it says in Galatians 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.65,0:23:32.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"Have ye suffered so many things in vain?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.82,0:23:34.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.95,0:23:36.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned from the get-go in the joint to get in touch
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.99,0:23:40.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with the soft nurturing side of myself, the feminine side.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.67,0:23:50.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm open to some sort of discussion on compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.59,0:23:54.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall be my compensation, sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.14,0:23:57.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,for being held down and sodomized by four white guys
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.43,0:23:59.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,or four black guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:02.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall my compensation be the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.98,0:24:06.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the formula for compensation, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.40,0:24:08.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How about $10,000 in cash?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.70,0:24:12.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do I...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.99,0:24:18.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, let's just break that down. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.74,0:24:20.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Now, wait, wait, wait a minute. - Let's just break it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.87,0:24:22.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, that figure just came to the top of my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.33,0:24:23.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's just say, for argument's sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.00,0:24:27.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,let's say $20,000, let's say $30,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.21,0:24:29.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Say... I'll tell you what. Let's say $50,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.51,0:24:32.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,$50,000 into 14 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.88,0:24:36.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourteen years times 365 days is about...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.18,0:24:38.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I say about 5,000 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.01,0:24:43.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you divide that by $50,000, and that's like $10 a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.15,0:24:46.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even minimum wage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.69,0:24:50.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,To say nothing about the family that I lost, the respect that I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.03,0:24:52.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you really, really understand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.07,0:24:55.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,what we're talking about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.24,0:24:56.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourteen years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.03,0:25:00.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops. Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.83,0:25:01.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta git.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.95,0:25:03.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm late for another appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.09,0:25:11.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, my man, I got some good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.13,0:25:13.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I got the bank, I got the account number.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.13,0:25:14.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Great. I'll call your son-in-law's lawyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.22,0:25:18.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Bowden, your wife's on line one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:20.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ask her to hold. I got to make a quick call.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.64,0:25:22.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't make that call, Sam. The way I'd...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.81,0:25:24.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Bowden, she says it's urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.36,0:25:30.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.99,0:25:36.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,...these kind of horrible, high-pitched howls.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.53,0:25:39.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They sounded like he was screaming,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.24,0:25:40.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and then Dani came running in,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.66,0:25:41.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.45,0:25:45.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I called the vet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.08,0:25:49.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it was so weird because
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.84,0:25:55.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,it was like he was winding down,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.09,0:25:59.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,just winding down like an old clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.80,0:26:02.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, all of a sudden, he just stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.52,0:26:06.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He had this kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.35,0:26:11.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,His eyes just wide open, and this kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.57,0:26:15.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,surprised look.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.95,0:26:18.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.70,0:26:23.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.33,0:26:28.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He just died, before the vet even got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.04,0:26:32.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did the vet say?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.34,0:26:34.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That he was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.55,0:26:35.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Poisoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.09,0:26:37.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of a poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.01,0:26:40.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what kind of poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.59,0:26:41.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.68,0:26:43.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leigh, I told you not to let him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.22,0:26:44.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't let him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.56,0:26:45.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then how...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.68,0:26:47.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- I didn't let him out! - Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.06,0:26:50.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got an English Setter myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.94,0:26:53.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't cotton to dog killers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.36,0:26:56.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Trouble is, poisoning a dog is just a fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.11,0:26:59.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he's unemployed, he got to have money
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.78,0:27:01.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,or we'll bust him for vagrancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.45,0:27:04.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give him a full-body strip search.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.79,0:27:07.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Jerk a knot in his tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.46,0:27:09.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.08,0:27:14.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They got so many ways on the books to lean on an undesirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.38,0:27:17.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll feel about as welcome around here
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.21,0:27:18.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,as a case of yellow fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.42,0:27:19.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hands against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.72,0:27:21.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Spread them. Spread them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.01,0:27:24.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- That him? - Face the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.56,0:27:25.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,One-way mirror, Mr. Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.97,0:27:27.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't know you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.60,0:27:29.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Yeah, that's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.64,0:27:31.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get the shirt off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.60,0:27:34.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.15,0:27:36.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Just pass it over to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.40,0:27:39.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.03,0:27:41.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Knock off the shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.78,0:27:45.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand them to the other officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.74,0:27:49.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Pass them to him. Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.37,0:27:53.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Let's put the arms out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.71,0:27:55.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Put your arms out straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.17,0:27:59.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Roll your palms. - Do what he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.01,0:28:04.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn around, slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.77,0:28:16.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know whether to look at him or read him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.32,0:28:21.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand still.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.28,0:28:27.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- One more step for you. - You know the routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.12,0:28:30.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Against the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.46,0:28:34.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We searched his apartment. His car registration and everything's in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.96,0:28:38.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no guns or any other weapons. But we found these.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.13,0:28:43.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady's savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.80,0:28:44.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,$30,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.68,0:28:47.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, see, his mother died while he was serving
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.97,0:28:50.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and the farm got sold off. He got the proceeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.31,0:28:53.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's got money. Where does that leave us?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.31,0:28:55.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, at the very least, we nail him for the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.15,0:28:56.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.48,0:28:58.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You let the dog out. Cady abducted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.11,0:28:59.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.48,0:29:02.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't let the dog out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.57,0:29:04.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady came into your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.70,0:29:06.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's illegal entry with intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.53,0:29:09.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But he didn't come in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.99,0:29:14.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I'm not a cop. I don't know exactly how he did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.75,0:29:17.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just know that he did it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.58,0:29:19.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not good enough, Mr. Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.55,0:29:21.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you're a lawyer. You damn well know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.76,0:29:23.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off the pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.80,0:29:30.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sooner or later, he's gonna screw up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.39,0:29:32.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the sheriff assured me
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.10,0:29:34.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that they always do. He's an ex-con.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.18,0:29:36.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he's going to get the message in no uncertain terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.77,0:29:38.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd still like to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.71,0:30:04.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Dani, how come you didn't join up with them? You can tap.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.88,0:30:07.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you can do that. You can tap dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.09,0:30:11.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to once, but I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.48,0:30:22.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.69,0:30:23.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.86,0:30:30.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's staring at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.24,0:30:31.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.62,0:30:38.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.46,0:30:40.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hot as a firecracker on the 4th of July.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.84,0:30:45.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're damn lucky to have her, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.13,0:30:46.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.63,0:30:48.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.59,0:30:49.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.89,0:30:57.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch my arm. Watch my arm. It might be broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.23,0:30:59.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you, buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.44,0:31:01.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no right to be pushing me around like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.27,0:31:02.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just watching the parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.40,0:31:03.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't pranking on nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.57,0:31:04.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.03,0:31:07.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you getting so upset about?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.74,0:31:09.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky I don't sue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.28,0:31:12.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.66,0:31:13.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.74,0:31:15.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I am. I am. I am settled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.00,0:31:18.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.37,0:31:19.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.46,0:31:21.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who was that? - It's no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.50,0:31:22.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who was that? - No one. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.00,0:31:26.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The fellow with the tie, his wife took him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.30,0:31:28.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he really hurt his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.76,0:31:29.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.22,0:31:34.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an awfully strong drink you've got there, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.89,0:31:36.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.52,0:31:40.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You just put a little goldfish in it, and you'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.98,0:31:43.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be having a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.98,0:31:45.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been practicing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.48,0:31:46.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Practicing for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.65,0:31:48.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How to fall on the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.78,0:31:50.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A life of debauchery.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.20,0:31:51.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"Debauch," what?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.61,0:31:54.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Debauchery. It's a three-syllable word. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.12,0:31:58.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Making fun of me? That's okay. No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.66,0:31:59.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not. I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.91,0:32:00.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I made you blush.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.00,0:32:01.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Blush?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.04,0:32:05.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You're now the color of your shirt, scarlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.21,0:32:11.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no business getting stuck on a guy who was married.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.72,0:32:13.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.39,0:32:14.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.01,0:32:17.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,God only knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.18,0:32:19.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now aren't I the bozo on this bus?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.68,0:32:24.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God. Lest you think that I slept with this particular
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.23,0:32:26.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- married guy... - That's your business. Not mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.19,0:32:27.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to make it sound like
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.65,0:32:28.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been through a busload of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.74,0:32:32.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the way it sounded to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.32,0:32:33.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the first.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.49,0:32:34.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.62,0:32:36.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He was, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.16,0:32:37.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.37,0:32:39.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, boy. - Tell it to the judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.08,0:32:44.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually the rat stood me up today.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.71,0:32:45.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.79,0:32:47.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes! - What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.34,0:32:48.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.71,0:32:51.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, now it's my turn. Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.80,0:32:52.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Where am I from? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.97,0:32:54.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're gonna love this. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.05,0:32:59.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the Georgia State Correctional Facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.40,0:33:08.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you think I'm joking? That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.11,0:33:09.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just got released from prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.73,0:33:13.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God. This is the way my day has been turning out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.78,0:33:16.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it reminds me of a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.74,0:33:19.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you want to hear it? - Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.28,0:33:20.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Liven up the night. - All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.45,0:33:24.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,An unmarried woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.08,0:33:25.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, that's not it. An unmarried woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.79,0:33:27.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, get the joke straight, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.46,0:33:29.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up. Shut up. Let me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.34,0:33:31.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,An unmarried woman, she meets a guy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.30,0:33:34.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and he tells her he just got out of prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.26,0:33:36.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"What did you do?" She asks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.09,0:33:38.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"I hacked my wife into 52 pieces with a chain saw."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.43,0:33:44.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She says, "So, you're single?"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.27,0:33:46.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- That's even funnier. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.98,0:33:49.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Could I ask you something? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.44,0:33:51.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- What did you do? - I knew you were going to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.61,0:33:53.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I hacked my wife into 52 pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.74,0:33:55.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid you were gonna say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.45,0:33:59.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm a very small person, so maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.20,0:34:01.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can hack you into 40 pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.58,0:34:07.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.79,0:34:09.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"No, really, but what did you do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.88,0:34:16.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just... There was this protest march on this nuclear power plant,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.17,0:34:18.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and so when they came to arrest us,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.80,0:34:21.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,this macho sheriff got a tad rough with the lady behind me,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.47,0:34:23.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,so, I popped the little bastard,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.56,0:34:25.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,so they gave me a little time for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.73,0:34:29.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm drinking a Sea Breeze. I hope you can afford them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.77,0:34:30.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But you gotta stay sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.02,0:34:34.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ain't sober, then you're taking your chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.15,0:34:36.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I'm just one hell of an animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.32,0:34:38.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? Do tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.32,0:34:43.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get you on this side, doll. Let's do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.95,0:34:45.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is Loretta anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.75,0:34:48.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the love of my life. She's no longer with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.21,0:34:49.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I was the love of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.50,0:34:52.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Chopped her up into 52 pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.47,0:34:58.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He hurt you like this, that married guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.63,0:34:59.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.72,0:35:00.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He hurt you like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.84,0:35:03.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, we never did anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.18,0:35:04.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He hurt you like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.68,0:35:06.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.85,0:35:08.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a rough one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.94,0:35:10.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How's this feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.40,0:35:16.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God. Am I under arrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.49,0:35:20.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not quite, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.78,0:35:26.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Officer, I swear, it's all a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.62,0:35:30.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That married guy hurt you like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.00,0:35:33.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because what he did to me hurt a lot worse than this!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.88,0:35:35.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.05,0:35:44.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got you now, bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.07,0:35:57.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, when did this key stop working?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.57,0:36:00.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Oh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.78,0:36:04.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder. A wire's missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.20,0:36:08.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A piano wire is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.33,0:36:10.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Was somebody fooling around with the piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.37,0:36:11.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.96,0:36:15.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah? - Mr. Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.84,0:36:18.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we might could have a little break here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.17,0:36:19.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.30,0:36:21.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can be there in a half hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.76,0:36:22.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, fine. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.47,0:36:24.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.80,0:36:26.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady raped another girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.35,0:36:30.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Rape? I thought you said it was battery.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.18,0:36:33.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah, the case was wobbly. I got it reduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.10,0:36:35.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember those days, old slippery Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.52,0:36:38.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Leigh. I just didn't want to alarm you or Dani.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.03,0:36:40.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? How old was that girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.28,0:36:41.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.95,0:36:43.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sixteen, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.08,0:36:52.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, my birthday is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.71,0:36:54.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Neighbors heard screams and called us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.46,0:36:57.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,When the perp drove off, somebody made his plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.38,0:36:59.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Max Cady. Good. - Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.46,0:37:02.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We got one bitty problem. The girl is scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.76,0:37:05.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She's claiming she fell down some stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.85,0:37:12.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.27,0:37:17.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't... Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.65,0:37:20.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.15,0:37:24.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You two know each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.53,0:37:30.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.49,0:37:33.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.08,0:37:38.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:40.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Lori, don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.59,0:37:47.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You stood me up at the club the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.51,0:37:50.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you didn't call.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.56,0:37:57.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And by last night, I was feeling pretty reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.19,0:38:01.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about what you said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.98,0:38:05.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that your wife, she didn't know I existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.45,0:38:11.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And I felt like I was going to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.50,0:38:16.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I showed you, all right, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.00,0:38:20.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I really showed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.09,0:38:27.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lori, listen to me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.72,0:38:33.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, look, this guy Cady, he's done this kind of thing before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.18,0:38:38.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, he's going to do this over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.69,0:38:42.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,unless you testify and we take him to court...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.11,0:38:43.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.36,0:38:45.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And press charges and testify.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.03,0:38:47.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lori. - Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.90,0:38:52.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, I know, I know how it works. I see it every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.24,0:38:55.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Only this time, I'm on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.00,0:39:00.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to explain why I was in a bar
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.71,0:39:04.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and how much I had to drink and what I was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.30,0:39:06.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not by the people I work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.67,0:39:10.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not by the guys that I see cross-examine other people on the stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.93,0:39:15.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,just crucify them and just laugh about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.27,0:39:19.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll even ask about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.23,0:39:24.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lori, listen to me. I don't care about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.27,0:39:26.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I care about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.74,0:39:29.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.86,0:39:32.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.95,0:39:36.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm terribly sorry, Lori. I'm just terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.96,0:39:40.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.04,0:39:43.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If all this is something personal
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.67,0:39:45.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,between you and the girl and Cady...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.30,0:39:46.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Personal? I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.80,0:39:49.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, come on, Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.26,0:39:50.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.59,0:39:52.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Only that there are some things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.09,0:39:54.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that are better handled quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.10,0:39:55.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.60,0:39:58.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This Cady guy is planning to rape my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.64,0:39:59.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not your problem anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.14,0:40:02.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't bust someone for planning to rape your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:04.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lawyer, Mr. Bowden. You know that damn well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.32,0:40:07.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Thanks all the same. - The way I'd handle it...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.40,0:40:09.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What, file a restraining order? I already did.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.65,0:40:11.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just think of this fellow Cady as a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.99,0:40:14.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The trick is to get him out of the brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.24,0:40:15.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now how do we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.91,0:40:18.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You stake out a couple of your goats and hide in a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.70,0:40:20.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you suggesting, Lieutenant?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.58,0:40:23.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That I use my family as bait? And then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.67,0:40:25.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What? I'm gonna hope that this psychopath
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.84,0:40:27.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,attacks my wife and child?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.67,0:40:29.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then what? Blow his head off?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.34,0:40:30.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a law officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.13,0:40:33.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be unethical of me to advise a citizen
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.84,0:40:35.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to take the law into his own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.93,0:40:38.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I suppose you must've misunderstood me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.43,0:40:39.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess I must've.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.68,0:40:43.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, pardon me all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.13,0:41:12.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's been harassing my family, but he's clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.76,0:41:15.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, cleverly, so that the law can't touch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.43,0:41:17.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Also I believe that he's able to slip
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.22,0:41:18.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,into the house and out undetected.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.97,0:41:20.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, is he out? I can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.72,0:41:23.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He's either out or he's in. I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.60,0:41:25.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't see through walls, Mr. Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.19,0:41:28.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not asking you to see through walls. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.98,0:41:30.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, why can't anybody do anything for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.94,0:41:32.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What good are cops and laws...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.99,0:41:34.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, Sam, Sam, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.82,0:41:36.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me explain something to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.74,0:41:39.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,See, the system is set up to handle generalized problems
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,like burglary and robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.25,0:41:45.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But if some lone creep out there targets you for some obscure reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.62,0:41:48.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the system is slow and skeptical. It's pathetic even.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.42,0:41:51.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your connection with this fellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.34,0:41:55.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I was his lawyer, his public defender.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.51,0:41:57.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But you shafted him somehow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.43,0:42:00.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, at least that's the way he perceives it. - Sam, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.43,0:42:03.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what you did. What did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.56,0:42:05.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He raped a 16-year-old girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.81,0:42:08.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a daughter around sixteen?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.31,0:42:10.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She's fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.52,0:42:12.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Here's the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.69,0:42:14.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do a background check on him,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.24,0:42:16.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,follow him for about a week and write you up a risk assessment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.36,0:42:17.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, good. Great, great.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.70,0:42:18.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the cops...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.78,0:42:20.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.20,0:42:21.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- His name's Max Cady. - You already told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.04,0:42:24.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just take it easy. Stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:27.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Dani, you can just relax because
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.92,0:42:31.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,your daddy has a private investigator on the payroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.21,0:42:33.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.63,0:42:37.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your feeling about him? What, Sam Spade?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.01,0:42:40.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mickey Spillane? Peter Gunn?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.60,0:42:43.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dirty Harry? Perry Mason?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.47,0:42:45.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, no. Perry Mason...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.14,0:42:46.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Perry Mason was a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.56,0:42:48.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, the minute I walked in this guy's office,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.48,0:42:49.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt totally relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.81,0:42:51.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, this guy is totally in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.90,0:42:53.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek deals with these types for a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.94,0:42:56.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He looked like he was going to enjoy...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.03,0:43:00.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes? - Yeah, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.82,0:43:03.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,After you left, I had this interesting conversation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.28,0:43:05.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with a C.O. Over at Statesboro prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.25,0:43:07.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm-hmm. Seems our man Cady had a job in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.66,0:43:08.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.75,0:43:10.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There was this other inmate working in there with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.38,0:43:12.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- he was an obstinate S. O.B. - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.59,0:43:13.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He hated Cady's cigar smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.00,0:43:16.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and he was always bitching and moaning about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.55,0:43:17.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, one day, they found him
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.80,0:43:19.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with his neck broke and his tongue bit off.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.76,0:43:21.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, Jesus. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.02,0:43:28.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They never could place Cady near the scene of the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.60,0:43:31.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if you want to call it that, at least not out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.73,0:43:36.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But the parole board, they kept him in for another seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.69,0:43:39.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-oh. The subject is on the move. Get a good night's sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.03,0:43:41.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Who was that? - Our private eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.37,0:43:43.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we were relaxed now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.54,0:43:47.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,New Essex County Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.91,0:43:51.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, room 5036, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.33,0:43:52.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,One minute, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.46,0:43:53.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.21,0:43:55.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.25,0:43:56.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, Lori, it's me, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.80,0:43:59.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lori, I just feel God-awful
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.13,0:44:00.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you got dragged into this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.55,0:44:01.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.72,0:44:04.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had any idea that Cady would hurt you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.51,0:44:06.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to get at me, I would have warned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.72,0:44:09.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know. I know. I'm glad you called.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.73,0:44:11.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Yeah, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.48,0:44:13.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.27,0:44:14.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.73,0:44:18.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you really determined
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.07,0:44:20.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,about moving back to Connecticut?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.74,0:44:22.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I've thought about it a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.74,0:44:25.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just think it's probably the best thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.08,0:44:28.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that maybe I could go back to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.62,0:44:32.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really going to miss you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.29,0:44:34.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Excuse me, Lori.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.33,0:44:36.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know, that sounds real good. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.25,0:44:38.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's gonna work out fine. I'll get right back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.42,0:44:40.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay. Bye. - All right, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.55,0:44:47.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I just don't know what I hate more,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.14,0:44:52.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that insipid tone or your stupid, sophomoric infidelities.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.73,0:44:55.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.44,0:44:57.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl that got beat up?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.61,0:44:58.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was the girl that got beat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.86,0:45:00.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lori Davis. I already told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.32,0:45:02.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She works at the county courthouse. She's a clerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.99,0:45:05.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And what? You're fucking her?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.95,0:45:08.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting choice, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.87,0:45:10.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Calling from our bedroom phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.79,0:45:12.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Leigh, why is it that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.79,0:45:15.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,whenever I have a private phone conversation,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.17,0:45:18.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you assume that I'm fucking someone, huh? Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.54,0:45:20.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why that psychopath chose her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.01,0:45:23.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes, that's why he chose her.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.17,0:45:25.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not fucking her in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.60,0:45:30.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you sleazy son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.56,0:45:31.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You son of a bitch! You son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.97,0:45:33.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn you! You son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.98,0:45:35.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! Leigh!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.73,0:45:37.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani is right downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.86,0:45:41.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Oh, honey, there's nothing the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.28,0:45:43.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I can see, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.15,0:45:47.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you promised to leave all that shit behind in Atlanta.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.16,0:45:48.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What shit?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.91,0:45:56.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Christ, what a waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.96,0:45:58.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The humiliation we went through
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.25,0:46:00.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,confessing all our dirty little secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.17,0:46:02.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in those horrible sessions with Dr. Hackett.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.34,0:46:04.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We talked that one damn incident to death, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.67,0:46:05.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Why did you bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.88,0:46:07.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you asked me to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.30,0:46:08.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, why did you bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.64,0:46:10.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you bother?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.26,0:46:14.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you bother with you and me? With the marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.64,0:46:17.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Uprooting me and Dani? Moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.40,0:46:19.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's what we decided to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.98,0:46:22.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- You said that you wanted to get out! - You don't get it, do you, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.15,0:46:23.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Leigh. What is it I don't get?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.36,0:46:24.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You just don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.61,0:46:26.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What... What don't I get?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.45,0:46:29.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why put us through all of that! Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.95,0:46:31.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Nadine?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.87,0:46:33.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Dani.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.70,0:46:35.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.12,0:46:39.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just losing my mind here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.75,0:46:43.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have the balls to walk out,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.17,0:46:44.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- if that's what you wanted.- Oh, what I wanted?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.88,0:46:47.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I was going to split, with you acting the way you acted.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.51,0:46:48.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Acting? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.97,0:46:52.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You did some acting. I don't remember doing any acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.35,0:46:53.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you don't remember doing any acting?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.56,0:46:55.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, hey, let me refresh your memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.35,0:46:57.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember not taking any work for three months?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.60,0:46:59.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember that? You remember not fixing any meals?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.60,0:47:01.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not on fucking trial here!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.65,0:47:04.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember crying every goddamn morning, afternoon, every evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.98,0:47:06.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.82,0:47:11.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I scared you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.74,0:47:14.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.50,0:47:18.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you think? You thought maybe I was going to kill myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.75,0:47:20.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Over you? - Who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.50,0:47:21.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You pompous ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.71,0:47:23.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God damn it, Leigh, who knew what you were gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.59,0:47:24.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't leave the bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.71,0:47:26.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I wish you could say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.55,0:47:29.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, look, isn't this what Dr. Hackett talked about?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.51,0:47:31.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Digging up the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.10,0:47:35.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the relevant issue here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.52,0:47:37.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,is whether I've been messing around in New Essex.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.52,0:47:39.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And I have not been.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.19,0:47:42.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as this girl goes, Lori, she's just a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.61,0:47:43.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that shouldn't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.40,0:47:45.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.65,0:47:47.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, you know when you gravitate to people
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.11,0:47:48.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in the same world as you...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.28,0:47:49.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You gravitate to women.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.95,0:47:51.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, Leigh, for Christ sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.36,0:47:53.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a lawyer, she's a clerk. She looks up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.53,0:47:56.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She's just infatuated. I can't help that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.79,0:48:03.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Leigh, I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.46,0:48:06.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this whole thing has...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.71,0:48:12.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep feeling that there is some animal out there stalking us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.80,0:48:15.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he wants to hurt us in the worst way
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.81,0:48:19.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and that's got me frightened to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.85,0:48:25.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are scared, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.36,0:48:26.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.82,0:48:28.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody finally got to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.49,0:48:32.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Leigh, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.91,0:48:34.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that this guy beat and raped her
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.03,0:48:38.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because he knew that she wouldn't testify,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.12,0:48:40.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that she wouldn't press charges,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.75,0:48:42.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because she knows the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.92,0:48:44.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, she works in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.67,0:48:47.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She knows that she'd be on trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.01,0:48:52.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, because she wouldn't testify, you would assume that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.55,0:48:55.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,there was something going on between us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.01,0:48:57.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it would cause a rift.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.98,0:49:03.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That we'd be much more vulnerable to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.32,0:49:11.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we talked about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.82,0:49:13.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because now we can work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.28,0:49:15.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We can beat that son of a bitch,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.53,0:49:18.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the two of us together, working as a team.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.83,0:49:23.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.71,0:49:27.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, this is great. This is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.21,0:49:28.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.71,0:49:30.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.68,0:49:43.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.23,0:49:44.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I haven't ordered yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.56,0:49:47.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That fellow over there sent this over, paid for and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.77,0:49:48.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.32,0:49:50.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.40,0:49:52.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy who is just leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.74,0:49:56.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.82,0:49:59.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Cady, come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.66,0:50:02.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.54,0:50:05.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been in a real bad mood lately. Shame, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.92,0:50:07.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what you can do to brighten my mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.67,0:50:10.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - Get the hell out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.42,0:50:12.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean just this whole town,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.55,0:50:14.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean the whole goddamn state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.42,0:50:16.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to see you, I don't want to hear you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.18,0:50:18.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't want to smell you. Now, leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.51,0:50:20.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I like... Are you my friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.60,0:50:21.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.39,0:50:24.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. 'Cause I thought maybe you were my friend
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.27,0:50:26.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because I like to plan my comings and goings with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.52,0:50:27.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you're not my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.77,0:50:28.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're planning my comings and goings,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.90,0:50:29.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd call that presumptuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.06,0:50:32.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I'd call it downright rude,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.32,0:50:33.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because I ain't your porch-baby, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.19,0:50:36.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Gee golly gosh. I sure am sorry I offended you,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.90,0:50:38.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you white trash piece of shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.07,0:50:41.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh-ooh. I got the all-over fidgets on that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.83,0:50:44.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You've really shaken me up. I'm shivering all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.33,0:50:46.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.79,0:50:49.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not necessary to lay a foul tongue on me, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.00,0:50:53.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I could get upset. Things could get out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.88,0:50:56.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, in self-defense, I could do something to you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.72,0:50:58.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that you would not like, right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.47,0:51:00.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Anytime you feel squirrelly, you just jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.59,0:51:04.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You threatening me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.97,0:51:06.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You catch on fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.06,0:51:08.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I'm well within my rights
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.48,0:51:09.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to be here and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.02,0:51:11.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If I stay here, what you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.90,0:51:14.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't give a rat's ass about your rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.15,0:51:16.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You just watch your step, and you know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.49,0:51:18.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do? Arrest me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.24,0:51:20.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You a cop? Or were you a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.16,0:51:22.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Or were you not good enough to remain on the force?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.41,0:51:24.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause, you know that's the feeling I'm getting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.16,0:51:29.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope you enjoyed your breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.09,0:51:39.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am, this belong to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.34,0:51:40.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.38,0:51:41.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.22,0:51:44.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might need it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.51,0:51:46.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to frighten you, but if a dogcatcher
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.81,0:51:48.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,comes across a dog without a license,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.48,0:51:49.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,he's liable to think he's a stray
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.69,0:51:52.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and do God knows what to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.86,0:51:56.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, our dog is...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.44,0:51:58.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.69,0:52:00.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh, what a shame. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.11,0:52:02.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Man's best friend and all. Woman's, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.45,0:52:06.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Even without closing my eyes, I can picture him,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.83,0:52:10.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,big, friendly, shaggy, asleep at your feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.87,0:52:12.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,keeping you company while you're trying
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.67,0:52:15.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to finish up those pesky little sketches.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.84,0:52:21.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're Max Cady, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.51,0:52:27.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, you better get the hell out of here before I call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.31,0:52:29.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.10,0:52:30.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just giving you back your dog collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.52,0:52:31.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not on your property.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.85,0:52:33.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what'd you come out here for, you want to look around?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.06,0:52:36.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead, Mr. Cady, take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.07,0:52:38.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Nice house. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.32,0:52:41.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a nice house. You satisfied now you've seen it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.91,0:52:45.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Or is there more? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.16,0:52:47.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.62,0:52:49.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There is going to be more, isn't there, Mr. Cady? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.08,0:52:52.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't stop until you're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.04,0:52:56.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I be happy, Leigh, when you're not happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.25,0:52:59.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know anything about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.30,0:53:00.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what I see, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.59,0:53:01.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.76,0:53:05.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to know what you looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.55,0:53:07.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting to see your face,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.22,0:53:09.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but you know now that I see you,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.77,0:53:12.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you are just repulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.06,0:53:14.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- I understand. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.44,0:53:16.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm not your type. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.44,0:53:18.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All that prison time made me coarse.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.77,0:53:21.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'm covered in too many tattoos, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.99,0:53:23.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But, you see, there's not a whole hell of a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.78,0:53:27.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to do in prison but desecrate your flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.62,0:53:29.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it didn't have to be that way for either of us
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.62,0:53:32.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if your husband hadn't betrayed us both.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.08,0:53:35.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? We might have been different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.12,0:53:37.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We might have been happy, Leigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.21,0:53:39.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, someone's on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.88,0:53:41.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.80,0:53:42.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come out here!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.14,0:53:55.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam. Hey, Sam. Yo, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.15,0:53:58.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, I thought I'd catch you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.07,0:54:01.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that little smart aleck made me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.94,0:54:02.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He what?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.03,0:54:04.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it wasn't my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.11,0:54:05.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He was looking to be covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.45,0:54:07.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. There is a lot of cutsie-cutsie
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.28,0:54:08.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in that little prick, isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.45,0:54:09.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.53,0:54:10.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know where he was today?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.74,0:54:13.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,At the public library reading Thus Spake Zarathustra
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.91,0:54:16.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,by Friedrich Nietzsche, he's this German philosopher.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.12,0:54:17.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that God is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.33,0:54:18.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,God is dead. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.50,0:54:20.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, we can keep going this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.25,0:54:22.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's going to get awful expensive, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.92,0:54:25.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, look, I'm not so concerned about days.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.72,0:54:27.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just stay on him a few more nights, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.59,0:54:29.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, do you really want to resolve this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.55,0:54:31.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'd love to resolve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.97,0:54:33.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I got a suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.43,0:54:36.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's men that can be hired, by me,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.60,0:54:38.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to do a little job on Cady, a little hospital job.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.98,0:54:44.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we talking about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.74,0:54:46.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Two pieces of pipe and a bicycle chain.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.32,0:54:49.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.03,0:54:51.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't be so scary after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.45,0:54:52.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a lawyer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.62,0:54:53.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- We agree that I'm a lawyer? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.24,0:54:55.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, maybe 2,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.58,0:54:57.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,we'd have taken this guy out and stoned him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.96,0:55:01.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't operate outside the law. The law is my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.38,0:55:09.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, I'm home! Where is everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.51,0:55:10.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.01,0:55:15.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Evening, ladies. Oh, chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.27,0:55:19.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How is everything? Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.23,0:55:21.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. -Good. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.07,0:55:27.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He was here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.49,0:55:36.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.70,0:55:37.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Danielle?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.41,0:55:39.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Miss Danielle Bowden?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.83,0:55:40.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.21,0:55:43.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This is your new teacher calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.25,0:55:44.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,From English or Drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.75,0:55:45.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.59,0:55:47.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So how you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.67,0:55:48.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.01,0:55:50.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm just going down the list,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.93,0:55:52.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,greeting my summer students.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.26,0:55:55.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You sound kind of down.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.18,0:55:56.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.56,0:56:00.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's just been stuff going on around here, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.60,0:56:02.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Anything I can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.31,0:56:03.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.61,0:56:06.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, shit happens, you know, like the T-shirt says.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.86,0:56:07.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.19,0:56:13.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, Danielle, all that negativity, you can use that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.99,0:56:16.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.66,0:56:18.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm the kind of teacher that takes
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.54,0:56:20.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,a very personal interest in his kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.33,0:56:21.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And don't mind me if I tell you everything
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.04,0:56:24.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you're going through, it's okay, go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.92,0:56:26.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The awkwardness you feel, say,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.13,0:56:27.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,when you're walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.30,0:56:30.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and some leering fool is making fun of your sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.63,0:56:32.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the turmoil you feel, extra bad when
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.63,0:56:34.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that particular time of the month comes around,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.80,0:56:37.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the anger you feel that your mom and dad
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.10,0:56:38.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,won't let you just grow up
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.39,0:56:40.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and be yourself, be a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.98,0:56:42.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Go with it. Don't suppress or deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.98,0:56:45.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Use it in your life and your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.19,0:56:48.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.99,0:56:52.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's... I'll have to think about all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.24,0:56:58.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, class is tomorrow in Room 110, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.24,0:57:01.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's been changed to the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.50,0:57:03.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, what better place for drama, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.54,0:57:04.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.71,0:57:08.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And remember, Danielle,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.25,0:57:11.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you can use all those fears to draw upon and learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.88,0:57:14.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know this little tune?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.28,0:57:41.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you can trust in me, because I'm a do-right man, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.83,0:57:45.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, 'night now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.96,0:57:48.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.80,0:57:54.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, honey, I think maybe I should walk you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.05,0:57:58.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's okay, Mom. There's a lot of people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.72,0:58:00.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right here at 4:00 to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.89,0:58:02.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay. Bye. - Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.89,0:58:07.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think summer session was gonna be so crowded.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.94,0:58:09.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not. They're just having a big meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.57,0:58:11.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,about next fall's chorus program.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.03,0:58:13.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go downstairs for Drama. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.07,0:58:15.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.28,0:59:02.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.04,0:59:08.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Nadine?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.97,0:59:25.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here for the Drama class.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.77,0:59:32.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.32,0:59:34.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.90,0:59:36.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I busted?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.49,0:59:38.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - I hope not.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.53,0:59:41.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't smoke grass in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.32,0:59:43.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Privilege of the profession.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.66,0:59:47.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Eases inhibitions. You down here for Drama?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.45,0:59:48.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.83,0:59:51.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the Drama teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.25,0:59:53.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're, let me guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.42,0:59:57.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cecile James?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.01,1:00:01.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm Danielle Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.01,1:00:04.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Danielle. Oh, we spoke last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.76,1:00:05.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.18,1:00:09.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry. How rude.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.52,1:00:11.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.02,1:00:13.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.98,1:00:18.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we're alone now...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.53,1:00:24.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.46,1:00:38.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.55,1:00:41.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.84,1:00:44.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.97,1:00:48.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Little trick I learned. Take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.56,1:00:53.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know when we spoke on the phone last night?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.73,1:00:54.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.52,1:00:59.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You really made sense to me
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.78,1:01:01.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and I thought a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.65,1:01:04.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are human truths, darling.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.24,1:01:05.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it's all about.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.49,1:01:07.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's what we deal with here.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.24,1:01:10.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,See the book you have, Thomas Wolfe?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.08,1:01:14.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all about self-discovery, the inner voyage.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.67,1:01:17.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I like the end
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.59,1:01:24.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,where Eugene's journey... It was really mystical, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.14,1:01:28.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it was almost like a pilgrimage.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.93,1:01:31.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Almost like a cop-out, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.27,1:01:34.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Although those were the facts of Wolfe's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.19,1:01:37.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The novel is what you would call a roman ?clef.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.94,1:01:39.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what that is?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.40,1:01:42.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.40,1:01:45.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, nonetheless, you can't escape
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.11,1:01:46.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,your demons just by leaving home.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.78,1:01:50.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Although writers do find new freedom when they relocate abroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.08,1:01:54.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Take Henry Miller. Have you read his trilogy?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.12,1:01:55.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Plexus, Nexus and Sexus?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.08,1:01:59.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. No. - You haven't read that?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.05,1:02:01.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're missing something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.30,1:02:06.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know what? I did read Tropic of Cancer.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.64,1:02:09.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just parts of it, though,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.30,1:02:13.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because I had to sneak it off my parents' shelf, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.73,1:02:18.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But his descriptions are pretty vivid, I would say.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.98,1:02:21.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In one of the novels, I don't recall which,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.53,1:02:24.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,he describes an erection as a piece of lead with wings on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.53,1:02:27.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't read that part.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.24,1:02:28.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not. You're not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.07,1:02:31.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Your parents don't want you to achieve adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.20,1:02:32.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.33,1:02:35.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They know the pitfalls of adulthood, all that freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.58,1:02:37.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They know it only too well.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.46,1:02:41.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Temptation to stray, deflecting their guilt and anger onto you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.46,1:02:44.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,for a crime that's not even a crime, for smoking grass.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.68,1:02:52.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.81,1:02:54.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.60,1:02:57.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I from?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.73,1:02:59.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. - Where do you think I'm from?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.48,1:03:02.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.19,1:03:04.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If I told you, you going to get mad at me?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.94,1:03:06.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.20,1:03:14.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm from the black forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.04,1:03:19.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.71,1:03:23.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the Drama teacher, are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.71,1:03:26.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'm the big bad wolf.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.68,1:03:29.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.30,1:03:34.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're that guy that's been hanging around the house?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.56,1:03:38.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one that killed my mom's dog?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.56,1:03:40.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom's dog was killed?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.81,1:03:41.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.73,1:03:45.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.40,1:03:46.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.53,1:03:48.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a damn shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.74,1:03:51.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.45,1:03:53.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of dog was it?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.20,1:03:56.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. He was just...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.58,1:03:58.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He was fluffy, and...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.21,1:04:01.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fluffy?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.42,1:04:03.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.30,1:04:08.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So you didn't do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.17,1:04:10.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I didn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.10,1:04:16.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.47,1:04:17.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.68,1:04:21.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So why... What are you doing here, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.65,1:04:24.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I came to meet you, to be honest with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.74,1:04:29.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? I mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.86,1:04:30.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.45,1:04:35.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to meet you, see what you're like.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.95,1:04:38.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I see you're a nice person. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.46,1:04:43.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to hurt me, are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.04,1:04:46.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to hurt you at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.13,1:04:48.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no hurting here, Danielle.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.67,1:04:51.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Between us, there's no anger, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.01,1:04:54.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a search for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.14,1:04:58.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, did you judge me, did you get angry at me
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.31,1:04:59.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,when you caught me smoking the grass?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.06,1:05:01.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.27,1:05:02.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.81,1:05:05.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But your parents, they judged you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.81,1:05:07.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They got plenty angry at you, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.02,1:05:09.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.82,1:05:12.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They punished you for their sins.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.32,1:05:14.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did they do?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.82,1:05:15.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.03,1:05:20.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad... They just yelled a whole lot
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.50,1:05:23.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and my mom cried
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.21,1:05:26.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and my dad said I couldn't drive the Cherokee.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.84,1:05:29.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I would say they punished you for their sins,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.30,1:05:30.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and you resent that,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.71,1:05:32.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and you should resent it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.55,1:05:36.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But Professor do-right has a little advice for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.22,1:05:38.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't damn them.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.85,1:05:40.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't judge them. Just forgive them,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.68,1:05:42.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,for they know not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.35,1:05:45.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.85,1:05:47.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you hate my father?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.48,1:05:50.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't hate him at all. Oh, no. I pray for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.53,1:05:53.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to help him.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.74,1:05:56.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, we all make mistakes, Danielle.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.41,1:06:00.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I have. But at least we try to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.54,1:06:01.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.29,1:06:03.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.96,1:06:05.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But your daddy, he don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.38,1:06:11.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Every man carries a circle of hell around his head like a halo.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.21,1:06:12.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Your daddy, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.51,1:06:17.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Every man, every man has to go through hell to reach his paradise.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.26,1:06:20.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what paradise is?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.93,1:06:22.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No. - Salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.06,1:06:26.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause your daddy's not happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.14,1:06:27.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mommy's not happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.10,1:06:31.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And you know what? You're not happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.86,1:06:33.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.07,1:06:35.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.03,1:06:42.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You thought about me last night, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.58,1:06:48.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.58,1:06:50.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.34,1:06:56.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I think I might have found a companion,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.05,1:07:00.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,a companion for that long walk to the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.06,1:07:06.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if I put my arm around you?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.99,1:07:21.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.45,1:07:25.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.25,1:07:27.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.54,1:08:57.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek, where the hell have you been, for Christ sake?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.71,1:08:59.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He came at my daughter at school.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.21,1:09:00.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me to watch him nights.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.34,1:09:02.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm watching him nights. What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.59,1:09:05.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife, Leigh, she found some marijuana
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.22,1:09:06.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in one of Dani's schoolbooks.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.64,1:09:09.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know if Cady gave it to her or exactly what happened,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.56,1:09:11.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but she's scared and she won't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.39,1:09:13.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But now this has gone far enough. It's got to stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.81,1:09:14.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You phone the cops?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.90,1:09:16.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't phone the cops.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.48,1:09:17.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, what did you call them?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.73,1:09:19.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You call them "Slow, skeptical, pathetic, even."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.78,1:09:21.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dani. - No, Leigh, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.65,1:09:23.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just hold on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.49,1:09:28.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek, look, I want to hire those three guys,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.70,1:09:30.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you remember, the hospital job.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.37,1:09:33.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it done, the sooner the better.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.87,1:09:35.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Three men's going to cost you a grand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.63,1:09:36.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I know that's not chicken feed,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.88,1:09:38.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but you don't wanna go with less than three.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.46,1:09:40.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better to overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.59,1:09:42.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. You'll have the money in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.47,1:09:44.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Then we'll be on for tomorrow night.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.26,1:09:47.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And Sam, you'll feel good about this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.27,1:09:52.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.45,1:10:07.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you notice these young people?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.95,1:10:09.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't look very happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.53,1:10:12.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They're committed to their professions and to their ambitions,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.25,1:10:13.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but they're not committed to each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.79,1:10:15.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady, shut up and listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.25,1:10:19.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't leave...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.50,1:10:21.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't leave my family alone
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.46,1:10:23.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and if you don't get out of here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.67,1:10:26.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you're going to be hurting like you never dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.76,1:10:29.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you repeat that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.85,1:10:30.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I said,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.97,1:10:33.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if you don't get out of here,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.22,1:10:35.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you're going to be hurting like you never dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.31,1:10:37.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- A threat? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.98,1:10:39.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You bet your ass that's a threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.81,1:10:41.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have thought of relocating
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.86,1:10:44.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,somewhere where I'd be more appreciated, California, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.99,1:10:47.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I could teach earthquake preparedness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.16,1:10:51.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But then it hits me, I love New Essex, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.95,1:10:55.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, where else could I just casually confer
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.16,1:10:56.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with an old colleague?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.41,1:10:59.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not colleagues. Do you understand that? We're not colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.88,1:11:01.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Still think you're better than me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.09,1:11:02.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't think I'm better than you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.46,1:11:03.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the goddamned point.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.01,1:11:05.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. 'Cause if you're not better than me,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.97,1:11:07.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,then I can have what you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.43,1:11:09.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I have?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.89,1:11:11.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A wife, a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.02,1:11:17.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to teach you the meaning of commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.52,1:11:19.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fourteen years ago, I was forced to make
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.73,1:11:21.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,a commitment to an eight-by-nine cell
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.65,1:11:24.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and now you're going to be forced to make a commitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.78,1:11:27.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say I'm here to save you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.53,1:11:31.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.03,1:11:34.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Check out the Bible, Counselor,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.95,1:11:36.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the book between Esther and Psalms.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.75,1:11:45.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani? Dani?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.01,1:11:49.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.47,1:11:51.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- What? - Is everything all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.89,1:11:52.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.22,1:11:58.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't going to work, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.52,1:11:59.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What isn't going to work?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.23,1:12:02.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Locking us in, hiding us from the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.06,1:12:04.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't be so dramatic, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.07,1:12:06.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Making me stay out of school.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.73,1:12:08.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going back to school tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.74,1:12:09.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And put some clothes on.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.95,1:12:11.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not a little kid anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.61,1:12:14.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah? Then why am I going back to school tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.28,1:12:15.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.62,1:12:18.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That's none of your concern, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.16,1:12:24.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad, he didn't force himself on me, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.71,1:12:27.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you'd like to think that he did.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.84,1:12:30.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But I think he was...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.76,1:12:34.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was just trying to make a connection with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.26,1:12:36.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- You know? - Now, Dani,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.97,1:12:38.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.52,1:12:41.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right? No. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.60,1:12:45.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No. There will never be any connection
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.57,1:12:48.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,between you and Max Cady.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.15,1:12:51.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You understand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.66,1:13:02.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he touch you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.13,1:13:09.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you laughing about? Why are you smiling?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.63,1:13:12.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you a question. Did he touch you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.51,1:13:15.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, wipe that smile off your face!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.39,1:13:17.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you, did he touch you?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.56,1:13:26.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, wait, Dani. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.48,1:13:28.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.11,1:13:31.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, honey. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.03,1:13:34.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.14,1:13:59.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Max?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.89,1:14:43.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Come on. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.72,1:14:45.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.88,1:15:19.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.14,1:15:21.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.01,1:15:24.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.39,1:15:28.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out, come out, wherever you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.87,1:15:44.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I ain't no white trash piece of shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.91,1:15:46.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm better than you all.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.79,1:15:51.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can out-learn you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.00,1:15:54.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can out-read you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.05,1:15:59.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can outthink you, and I can out-philosophize you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.05,1:16:02.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm going to outlast you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.47,1:16:03.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You think a couple of whacks
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.93,1:16:06.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to my good-old-boy gut's gonna get me down?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.10,1:16:09.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to take a hell of a lot more than that, Counselor,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.48,1:16:11.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to prove you're better than me!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.07,1:16:18.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am like God, and God like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.36,1:16:21.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am as large as God.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.16,1:16:24.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"He is as small as I.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.24,1:16:28.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"He cannot above me nor I beneath him be."
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.50,1:16:33.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Silesius, 17th century.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.71,1:16:43.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.01,1:16:51.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be there?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.44,1:16:57.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.53,1:17:07.45,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if you're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.00,1:17:18.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.59,1:17:22.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're here, what the fuck's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.59,1:17:24.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck it!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.19,1:17:36.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got Mr. Kersek on one.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.52,1:17:37.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. I'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.82,1:17:38.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.82,1:17:41.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, you look tired. You get that writ?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.61,1:17:44.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, we got to get into that. Let me just grab this.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.07,1:17:46.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Kersek. - Look, I'm damn sorry about last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.95,1:17:48.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That son of a bitch could survive
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.12,1:17:49.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,a preemptive nuclear strike.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.33,1:17:50.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Hang on a second. Hang on a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.12,1:17:53.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom, I'm not doing it. I pulled a fast one
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.33,1:17:55.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's come back and it's bit me on the ass in a major way.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.00,1:17:57.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What you did was dumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.13,1:18:00.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm asking here is no big deal, Sam. This is my daughter!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.59,1:18:02.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Tom, it's perjury and it's bullshit
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.09,1:18:03.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and I'm not doing it! Now, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.01,1:18:05.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- All right? - All right. I'll be in my office.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.39,1:18:08.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom, who was that top criminal lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.18,1:18:09.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Lee Heller. - Kersek.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.01,1:18:11.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- We need to talk. - Trouble is
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.27,1:18:13.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if word gets out how Cady bushwhacked those poor bastards,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.64,1:18:15.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,it's gonna be a bitch to line up three new guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.27,1:18:17.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want three new guys. No more guys, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.86,1:18:19.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Heller, it's Sam Bowden
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.73,1:18:21.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,from Broadbent and Denmeyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.40,1:18:23.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom speaks very highly of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.74,1:18:24.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, he says you're the best,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.07,1:18:26.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and the best is what I need right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.36,1:18:28.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We froze our butts together in Korea.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.70,1:18:30.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How can I help you, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.12,1:18:32.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's a simple petition for a restraining order,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.95,1:18:34.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's been some complications.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.83,1:18:36.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I know this is short notice,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.29,1:18:38.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but look, I need this injunction.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.29,1:18:40.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, there's an ex-convict by the name of Max Cady,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.96,1:18:42.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,he's been harassing my family.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.09,1:18:45.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Mr. Bowden. I can't continue this conversation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.72,1:18:47.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, is there a more convenient time?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.51,1:18:50.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. The damn thing is I have a conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.18,1:18:51.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Now, what would that be? - Well, you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.06,1:18:54.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Cady retained my services as of yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.98,1:18:56.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He what?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.10,1:18:58.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, I see on my phone sheet
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.10,1:18:59.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Cady called this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.73,1:19:00.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm sure he'll fill me in...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.90,1:19:04.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait a minute, Lee. Now, look, this man is a psychotic.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.61,1:19:08.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears I'll be seeing you at that hearing after all.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.95,1:19:11.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you repeat that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.24,1:19:13.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I said if you don't leave...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.41,1:19:16.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't leave my family alone
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.33,1:19:18.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and if you don't get out of here,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.58,1:19:21.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you're gonna be hurting like you never dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.67,1:19:23.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A threat?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.71,1:19:26.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you bet your ass that's a threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.34,1:19:31.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You need only glance at my client to know
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.26,1:19:34.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that Mr. Bowden made good
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.56,1:19:37.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,on his heinous and cowardly threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.44,1:19:40.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as God arose to judgment
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.86,1:19:42.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to save all the meek of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.73,1:19:45.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope and pray you will do the same, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.73,1:19:47.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Honor,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.07,1:19:51.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Cady wouldn't have surreptitiously taped our meeting
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.37,1:19:53.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,unless he knew that he'd...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.16,1:19:59.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This court does not condone
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.00,1:20:04.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,feuds, vendettas or vigilantism.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.63,1:20:09.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me quote our great Negro educator, Mr. Booker T. Washington.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.22,1:20:14.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"I will let no man drag me down so low
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.64,1:20:18.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"as to make me hate him."
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.14,1:20:19.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.06,1:20:22.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I will grant the restraining order
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.81,1:20:26.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,not to validate the malice between you,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.40,1:20:31.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but in the interest of Christian harmony.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.07,1:20:36.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You may not come within 500 yards
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.24,1:20:40.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,of Mr. Maximilian Cady
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.58,1:20:46.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,until such time as the court may lift the injunction.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.96,1:20:51.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,King Solomon could not have adjudicated more wisely, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.72,1:20:57.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I am so offended by the philistine tactics of Mr. Bowden,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.47,1:21:01.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I petitioned the A. B.A. For his disbarment
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.77,1:21:04.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,on the grounds of moral turpitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.52,1:21:07.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you will excuse us, my client...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.61,1:21:08.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, son...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.73,1:21:10.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is due back at the hospital
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.07,1:21:17.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,for the results of his numerous X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.08,1:21:21.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek, I want a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.66,1:21:22.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a gun. I want a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.96,1:21:24.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You want a gun?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.21,1:21:25.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I need a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.96,1:21:27.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Know anything about guns? - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.13,1:21:28.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't believe in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.30,1:21:29.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I never had them around the house or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.84,1:21:30.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll get you a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.97,1:21:32.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of gun you want? Now, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.47,1:21:34.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, just something simple, something I can handle.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.55,1:21:37.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see what fits you. A.45...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.64,1:21:38.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Let me see your hands. - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.81,1:21:43.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- A.38 snub-nosed special. - Yeah. All right. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.14,1:21:45.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do. I can even teach you how to use it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.48,1:21:47.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- All right. Great. - The first lesson is this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.86,1:21:50.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think of it as shooting a man or trying to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.36,1:21:52.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Right. - Think of it as an extension of your fist.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.49,1:21:54.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just reaching out and knocking the man down.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.16,1:21:56.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.24,1:21:58.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Later on we can go out to the woods and shoot some trees, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.45,1:22:01.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be great. That'd be great. Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.25,1:22:05.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? What?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.08,1:22:06.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Well, Sam... - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.00,1:22:09.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I give you a gun. You pull it on Cady,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.55,1:22:10.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's gonna dawn on you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.67,1:22:11.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that shooting a man is different
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.76,1:22:13.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,than blowing holes in some tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.63,1:22:15.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Next thing, you know, you don't have my gun, Cady does.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.34,1:22:17.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no. You're gonna teach me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.47,1:22:18.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how to handle a gun.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.97,1:22:20.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't take it away from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.18,1:22:23.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Best-case scenario, you kill Cady dog-dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.14,1:22:27.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fifteen years to life. Do you realize that, Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.32,1:22:36.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Jesus! It's all fucked up, Kersek!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.07,1:22:38.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the law considers me
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.41,1:22:40.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,more of a loose cannon than Max Cady!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.33,1:22:42.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Some big-shit attorney has whipped
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.70,1:22:44.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,the A. B.A.'s ethics committee into a frenzy.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.46,1:22:48.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an emergency session in Raleigh over the assault.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.67,1:22:50.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How did they link that to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.54,1:22:54.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to warn Cady. I thought it was the decent thing to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.76,1:22:57.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'd scare him. And he was wired.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.47,1:23:02.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn fools.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.77,1:23:07.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This hearing, it's real important?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.90,1:23:13.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Only if I want to continue to practice law. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.53,1:23:15.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady isn't expected there, is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.07,1:23:19.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, no, no. Mr. Cady, he's beyond reproach.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.49,1:23:21.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- But you're required to be there. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.45,1:23:23.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,When is this hearing?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.58,1:23:25.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Thursday morning, 9:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.75,1:23:28.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The torture begins and lasts for two days.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.71,1:23:31.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to fly up the night before?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.96,1:23:33.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.05,1:23:35.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady's an opportunist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.92,1:23:37.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If he thinks you're gonna be out of town for two days,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.97,1:23:40.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that's going to be as tempting to him as shit is to a fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.43,1:23:43.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If Cady breaks into your home,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.10,1:23:44.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,he can be killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.89,1:23:46.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Justifiably.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.31,1:23:51.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But he won't show unless he's real sure you're not gonna be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.30,1:25:01.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a good trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.38,1:25:03.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Bye-bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.18,1:25:04.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Call us tonight, okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.26,1:25:05.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.02,1:25:17.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't miss the 9:20 to Raleigh?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.69,1:25:19.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid you did, sir. But there's a 10:20.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.07,1:25:21.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.24,1:25:24.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just have some very, very important papers for Samuel Bowden.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.70,1:25:25.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Was he on the 9:20?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.87,1:25:28.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't give out that information, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.37,1:25:30.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.66,1:25:33.54,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I could send it to him overnight,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.62,1:25:37.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but he might be back, for all I know, tomorrow morning, and I...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.71,1:25:40.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.42,1:25:43.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife and I have been in an accident, and he's our lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.80,1:25:47.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And if I don't get in touch with him, we could lose this case.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.06,1:25:50.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already lost our little daughter, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.23,1:25:53.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.06,1:25:56.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any way I can find out
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.31,1:25:59.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if he was on that flight and when he's coming back?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.11,1:26:01.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd really, really help us.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.37,1:26:13.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be back the day after tomorrow, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.08,1:26:15.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Bless your heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.93,1:26:32.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Go on. Go on in.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.27,1:26:36.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get down, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.15,1:26:44.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leigh. Leigh, give me a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.78,1:26:46.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You better slow down, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.03,1:26:48.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're outpacing me two-to-one since you started smoking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.07,1:26:51.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep track of how many I owe you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.62,1:26:54.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how'd it go at the airport?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.83,1:26:56.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we did our thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.12,1:26:57.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but we don't know if he saw us,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.54,1:26:59.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't even know if he was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.09,1:27:02.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Set the trap and we'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.67,1:27:03.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What if we don't want to see?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.21,1:27:05.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dani! - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.88,1:27:07.76,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he poisoned the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.09,1:27:10.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dani... - Sam, watch out for the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.14,1:27:13.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're not allowed to stand up, Dad, remember?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.73,1:27:20.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Cady go after her?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.98,1:27:22.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know Dani.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.23,1:27:24.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If she finds a palmetto bug in her bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.32,1:27:26.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,she takes it outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.15,1:27:28.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, she could never kill anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.61,1:27:30.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a six-foot palmetto bug?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.99,1:27:34.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.30,1:27:44.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.59,1:27:49.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a monofilament line. I got it from Sam's fishing gear.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.13,1:27:51.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,See, what I do is I stretch it across the windows and the doors
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.89,1:27:53.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and tie it to Dani's teddy bear here.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.97,1:27:55.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,If the bear moves a quarter of an inch,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.64,1:27:57.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll know if the holy ghost is sneaking in.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.38,1:28:31.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you reading?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.26,1:28:36.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Did Kersek quit?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.52,1:28:37.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.64,1:28:40.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that Cady said...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.56,1:28:42.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You want some answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.90,1:28:45.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.40,1:28:52.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know just how strong we are or how weak.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.91,1:28:56.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess the only way we're going to find that out
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.79,1:28:59.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,is just by going through this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.79,1:29:07.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that Cady said to read the book between Esther and Psalms.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.51,1:29:10.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is which one?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.63,1:29:12.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The Book of Job.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.43,1:29:18.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Job was a good man. He believed in God
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.39,1:29:21.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and God tested his faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.81,1:29:24.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He took away everything he had,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.73,1:29:27.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,even his children.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.79,1:29:46.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- It's hideous, this plan. - I mean, barbaric.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.79,1:29:50.30,en,,0000,0000,0000,,They're crazy. My dad's turned into some kind of...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.38,1:29:51.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.63,1:29:52.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Barbaric.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.30,1:30:00.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to your father. Do what they say. What else you can do?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.64,1:30:03.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave. We could go to the houseboat, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.69,1:30:05.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and get lost in any inlet.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.48,1:30:11.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.49,1:30:14.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stay outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.91,1:30:25.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna know what really disturbs me? It's killing this guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.63,1:30:28.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, taking a man's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.71,1:30:33.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can live with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.59,1:30:35.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You may have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.68,1:30:37.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Sam, just remember the plan. - I know the plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.68,1:30:41.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, it's premeditated. It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.52,1:30:44.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me an accomplice, an accessory, an abettor.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.44,1:30:47.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also excessive force.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.60,1:30:50.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam, the only thing excessive we could do to Cady
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.19,1:30:53.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,would be to gut him and eat his liver.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.19,1:30:54.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That might be excessive.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.40,1:30:56.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ, Kersek, I'm serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.74,1:30:58.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you're scared.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.49,1:31:02.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's okay. I want you to savor that fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.70,1:31:05.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the South evolved in fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.00,1:31:10.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear of the Indian, fear of the slave, fear of the damn Union.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.46,1:31:14.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The South has a fine tradition of savoring fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.19,1:31:33.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.40,1:31:36.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look over! Don't look.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.90,1:31:38.86,en,,0000,0000,0000,,She's making me nervous.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.24,1:31:41.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What would she normally do
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.91,1:31:43.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,if Sam wasn't around to run her home?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.99,1:31:45.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- She'd stay... - She'd stay over.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.25,1:31:48.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then, she stays over.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.98,1:34:22.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Leigh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.57,1:34:26.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- What? - Leigh.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.57,1:34:28.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how the dog died.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.66,1:34:31.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Sam, are you dreaming? - No. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.45,1:34:32.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had the weirdest feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.95,1:34:35.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,he was already in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.22,1:34:52.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't sleep, huh, Miss Graciela?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.35,1:34:53.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.31,1:34:57.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I think it's the humidity
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.40,1:34:59.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,that makes us all so thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.90,1:35:02.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.49,1:35:05.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My pop was a cop.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.11,1:35:07.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.99,1:35:10.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This was his favorite drink when he was on a stakeout.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.80,1:35:32.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I learned that in prison. You like?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.81,1:35:34.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,White trash piece of shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.94,1:35:45.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay here, Leigh.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.70,1:35:58.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.80,1:36:10.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, Dani, go back to your room. Go back to your room.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.80,1:36:12.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.18,1:36:16.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.19,1:36:20.73,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go down there, Sam.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.81,1:36:22.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:29.86,1:36:31.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Kersek?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.87,1:36:39.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.92,1:36:51.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, don't look.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.72,1:36:53.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God, Graciela!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.68,1:36:55.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dani, don't look. Don't look, Dani.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.43,1:36:58.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.60,1:37:01.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.52,1:37:09.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.75,1:37:25.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the piano wire.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.01,1:37:30.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.76,1:37:34.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to get this son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.14,1:37:35.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.68,1:37:38.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No! No! No!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.93,1:37:41.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.35,1:37:42.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna slit that son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.73,1:37:45.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him to stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.44,1:37:51.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,God, he might be out here! He might be out here!
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.82,1:38:32.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, listen, I've got Kersek's gun with me
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.57,1:38:36.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're gonna find the piano wire that Cady used in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.45,1:38:38.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know how this looks. I know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.66,1:38:41.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to flee a murder scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.37,1:38:43.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Lieutenant, now, you may know this and you may not,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.04,1:38:46.83,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but in the law, there's a thing called force majeure.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.92,1:38:49.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It means an unforeseeable act of God
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.50,1:38:52.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and it cancels all promises and obligations.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.30,1:38:54.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,So, legally speaking, all bets are off.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.05,1:38:58.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You find Max Cady and we'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.85,1:39:01.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.97,1:39:03.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He said we're fugitives.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.14,1:39:04.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:04.18,1:39:05.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That means we're doing something right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.96,1:39:37.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's that old mongrel dog of yours, Mrs. Bowden?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.02,1:42:00.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, I'll catch some fish.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.61,1:42:02.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you know, you don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.40,1:42:04.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got enough food here to last us a week.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.37,1:42:15.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:16.17,1:42:17.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.51,1:42:28.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only rain. A sheet of rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.06,1:42:34.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.23,1:42:35.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a squall.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.15,1:42:38.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go check the anchor.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.23,1:42:39.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Dad. Don't go out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.57,1:42:42.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Dani. Now, look, everything is okay. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:42.53,1:42:44.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We're on the river now, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.15,1:42:45.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a squall kicking up.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.35,1:43:13.64,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Graciela has a brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.72,1:43:15.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, she had...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.48,1:43:19.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sweetie.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.28,1:43:23.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get in touch with him right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.90,1:43:27.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.11,1:43:29.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We're making some tea.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.62,1:43:35.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.91,1:43:38.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.42,1:43:42.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hear you. It's windy out.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.84,1:44:25.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.55,1:44:27.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we moving?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.38,1:44:28.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Sam?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.93,1:44:33.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Evening, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.01,1:44:36.39,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know my husband has a gun?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.97,1:44:38.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Not this gun?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.39,1:44:39.52,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it this gun?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.60,1:44:40.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.94,1:44:43.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Resting up. He had a long, difficult day.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.36,1:44:46.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Danielle, I told you, you can't escape
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.07,1:44:48.78,en,,0000,0000,0000,,your demons just by leaving home.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.86,1:44:51.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.03,1:44:53.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My parents brought me here.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.28,1:44:54.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.37,1:44:56.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Sexus?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.41,1:44:58.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Back at the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.75,1:45:00.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.37,1:45:03.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I had hoped we could read aloud from it together.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.42,1:45:06.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.38,1:45:09.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I memorized some for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.51,1:45:10.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.88,1:45:12.72,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yeah. - Did you?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.01,1:45:16.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.18,1:45:17.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.93,1:45:19.98,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Which part?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.27,1:45:24.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The part...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.27,1:45:27.23,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know what part, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.78,1:45:31.07,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you did your homework.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.45,1:45:32.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.91,1:45:34.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What parts were they?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.74,1:45:38.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The good parts?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.49,1:45:40.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They were...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.08,1:45:41.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Were you a good girl?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.33,1:45:42.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.50,1:45:44.71,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd follow me here and...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.79,1:45:46.46,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know me pretty well, don't you, darling?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.54,1:45:48.63,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.26,1:45:51.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna get to know me a lot better, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.43,1:45:59.85,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you offering me something hot?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.43,1:46:03.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get something straight here.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.27,1:46:09.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I spent 14 years in an eight-by-nine cell
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.11,1:46:11.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,surrounded by people who were less than human.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.45,1:46:14.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,My mission in that time
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.78,1:46:16.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,was to become more than human.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.28,1:46:19.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.95,1:46:23.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Granddaddy used to handle snakes in church.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.83,1:46:25.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Granny drank strychnine.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.29,1:46:29.00,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you could say I had a leg-up, genetically speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.30,1:46:39.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna forgive you, Danielle, honey.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.14,1:46:42.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause I know that wasn't the real you, the true you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.98,1:46:45.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But I would like you to wait in the hold.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.27,1:46:50.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Danielle, Danielle, get in the hold.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.44,1:46:53.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Danielle!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.82,1:46:56.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Stop! - No!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.32,1:46:59.62,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:04.75,1:47:07.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to be born again, Mrs. Bowden?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.13,1:47:12.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,A few minutes alone with me, darling,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.84,1:47:15.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and you will be speaking in tongues.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.00,1:48:35.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Mrs. B.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:35.92,1:48:37.38,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't take umbrage,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.67,1:48:40.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but in the plan that I have formulated,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.51,1:48:43.97,en,,0000,0000,0000,,there's much more to it than just you and I just making love.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.22,1:48:48.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, that's just so commonplace and dreary.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:50.77,1:48:52.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Here and now, we have an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.98,1:48:54.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"What is that opportunity?" You ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.90,1:48:57.19,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, here and now, we have an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:48:57.28,1:49:00.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to depict and dramatize...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.45,1:49:01.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.49,1:49:05.12,en,,0000,0000,0000,,...both the heights and the depths
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.83,1:49:10.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,of a mama's true love of her daughter, if you all get my meaning.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.58,1:49:13.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on out, babe. Come on, darling. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.38,1:49:16.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out. Get up here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:16.25,1:49:17.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady, listen to me. This is between
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.63,1:49:19.17,en,,0000,0000,0000,,you and me. Leave them out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.55,1:49:23.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my night, Counselor. Don't you step on my lines.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.09,1:49:25.68,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.14,1:49:29.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Leigh?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.14,1:49:33.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me, Max. Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:35.65,1:49:38.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Max, since all this started,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.98,1:49:40.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've thought about you all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.99,1:49:46.28,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've tried to imagine what it must have been like for you
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.37,1:49:48.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,all those years, locked up in jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.74,1:49:53.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I've tried to imagine you and even your crimes
Dialogue: 0,1:49:53.87,1:49:57.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and how you must have felt in those moments that you did them.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:58.42,1:50:02.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I know about loss, Max.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.22,1:50:06.84,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know about losing time, even losing years.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.68,1:50:11.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And I know it doesn't compare to jail,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.18,1:50:16.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,but I can understand and I could share this with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:17.23,1:50:21.57,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, whatever it is that you've got planned,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.36,1:50:24.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to do it just with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:26.24,1:50:27.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,not with her,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.58,1:50:33.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because we have this connection.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.22,1:50:47.43,en,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.18,1:50:50.22,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.73,1:50:54.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That was real eloquent, Leigh.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:57.06,1:50:58.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Brave, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.94,1:51:02.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna thank you for conveying to me your very powerful emotions
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.94,1:51:05.15,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.95,1:51:13.37,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna enjoy this all the more.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.30,1:51:24.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:38.10,1:51:39.35,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.23,1:52:25.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,The people call Samuel J. Bowden!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:29.24,1:52:30.49,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you swear to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.57,1:52:32.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,and nothing but the truth, so help you, God?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.32,1:52:33.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady, somebody's got to man the boat.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.74,1:52:34.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading into unprotected water.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.04,1:52:36.24,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do you swear? - I'll do it, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:36.33,1:52:38.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You sit, Danielle! Don't you make light
Dialogue: 0,1:52:38.16,1:52:39.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,of your civic duty, darling. You're the jury.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.50,1:52:42.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, all right, okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.75,1:52:44.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I swear to tell the truth. What do you wanna know?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.75,1:52:46.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Was a prior sexual history ever prepared
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.96,1:52:48.51,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in connection with my defense?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.34,1:52:51.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Was a prior sexual history ever prepared
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.01,1:52:53.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,in connection with my defense?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:53.35,1:52:54.47,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.14,1:52:58.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Your Honor. I agree. That was argumentative.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:58.68,1:53:00.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,An investigator did prepare a prior
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.69,1:53:02.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,sexual history on the alleged victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.69,1:53:03.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,True?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.77,1:53:05.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I can ask leading questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.86,1:53:07.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He is a hostile witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.53,1:53:09.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you care to tell the court
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.11,1:53:10.95,en,,0000,0000,0000,,what the gist was of this report?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.03,1:53:13.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Cady, it was 14 years ago. I can't remember that.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.99,1:53:18.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,How can he answer when you're hitting him like that?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.12,1:53:19.70,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's perjuring himself, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:19.79,1:53:21.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,He knows damn well exactly what it said.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.75,1:53:22.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.88,1:53:24.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It said that she was promiscuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.75,1:53:27.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,It said that she had three different lovers in one month.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.30,1:53:29.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,At least three! At least three!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.21,1:53:31.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And did you show this report to the D. A?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.80,1:53:33.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:35.93,1:53:39.18,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I only discovered it by chance when I started representing myself
Dialogue: 0,1:53:39.27,1:53:40.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,six years into my sentence!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:40.89,1:53:42.48,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But there it was in the court file.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.56,1:53:45.02,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But back in '77, you buried it, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.11,1:53:47.77,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you care to tell the jury why?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.69,1:53:51.90,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you care to tell the court why?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:54.24,1:53:56.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I know he brutally raped her and he beat her.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.08,1:53:58.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to me! I'm standing here!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:59.95,1:54:01.50,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because she was promiscuous
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.58,1:54:03.04,en,,0000,0000,0000,,didn't give you the right to rape her!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.12,1:54:05.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You bragged to me that you beat two prior
Dialogue: 0,1:54:05.33,1:54:06.88,en,,0000,0000,0000,,aggravated rapes. You were a menace!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.96,1:54:10.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You were my lawyer! You were my lawyer!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.13,1:54:12.92,en,,0000,0000,0000,,That report could have saved me 14 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:13.01,1:54:14.01,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably right.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.09,1:54:15.93,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You self-righteous fuck!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:20.77,1:54:24.27,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Virgil, Counselor, and I'm guiding you through the gates of Hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:24.35,1:54:28.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We are now in the 9th circle, the circle of traitors.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:28.19,1:54:31.53,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Traitors to country, traitors to fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.61,1:54:33.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,traitors to God!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.78,1:54:35.91,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You, sir, are charged
Dialogue: 0,1:54:35.99,1:54:38.20,en,,0000,0000,0000,,with betraying the principles of all three!
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.28,1:54:40.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you please quote for me the American Bar Association's
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.08,1:54:43.79,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Rules of Professional Conduct, Canon seven?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.29,1:54:47.33,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"A lawyer should represent his client..."
Dialogue: 0,1:54:47.42,1:54:49.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"Should zealously represent his client
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.50,1:54:51.21,en,,0000,0000,0000,,"within the bounds of the law."
Dialogue: 0,1:54:51.30,1:54:54.09,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And I find you guilty, Counselor,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.17,1:54:56.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,guilty of betraying your fellow man,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:56.64,1:54:58.55,en,,0000,0000,0000,,guilty of betraying your country,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.64,1:55:00.60,en,,0000,0000,0000,,guilty of abrogating your oath,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.68,1:55:03.56,en,,0000,0000,0000,,guilty of judging me and selling me out!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.64,1:55:07.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And with the power vested in me by the kingdom of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:07.48,1:55:11.94,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I sentence you to the 9th circle of Hell!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:12.03,1:55:14.74,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you will learn about loss,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:14.82,1:55:18.66,en,,0000,0000,0000,,loss of freedom, loss of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.20,1:55:22.99,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you and I will truly be the same, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.16,1:55:25.16,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Danielle, get down on your knees.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.25,1:55:26.58,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you take off your clothes!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:26.67,1:55:28.25,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Down on your knees now!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.33,1:55:29.42,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.50,1:55:30.67,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Down on your knees!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.00,1:55:32.96,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Take off your clothes! Get down on your knees!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:34.80,1:55:38.26,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.85,1:55:44.10,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, take off your clothes! Off with your clothes!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:44.18,1:55:48.89,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You, Leigh, take off your clothes. Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.98,1:55:50.61,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.69,1:55:52.69,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Git! Git!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.77,1:55:54.40,en,,0000,0000,0000,,- No! - Git!
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.03,1:55:56.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, you're gonna learn to be an animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:56.90,1:55:59.03,en,,0000,0000,0000,,to live like an animal and to die like one.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.20,1:56:04.87,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your hand!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.28,1:56:39.82,en,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:39.91,1:56:41.41,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Go!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:06.09,1:59:09.14,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget about that restraining order, Counselor?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.22,1:59:11.81,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You're well within 500 yards!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:18.48,1:59:20.31,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here we are, Counselor,
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.40,1:59:23.44,en,,0000,0000,0000,,just two lawyers working it out!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.54,1:59:39.08,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.38,1:59:42.59,en,,0000,0000,0000,,You already sacrificed me, Counselor.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:28.09,2:00:31.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,On Jordan's stormy banks I stand
Dialogue: 0,2:00:31.14,2:00:34.05,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh who will come with me?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.14,2:00:47.65,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I am bound for the promised land
Dialogue: 0,2:02:39.60,2:02:44.06,en,,0000,0000,0000,,We never spoke about what happened, at least not to each other.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.48,2:02:51.36,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Fear, I suppose, that to remember his name or what he did
Dialogue: 0,2:02:51.44,2:02:54.11,en,,0000,0000,0000,,would mean letting him into our dreams.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:54.95,2:02:58.32,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And me, I hardly dream about him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:00.04,2:03:03.75,en,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, things won't ever be the way they were before he came.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.37,2:03:06.29,en,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all right
Dialogue: 0,2:03:06.37,2:03:10.34,en,,0000,0000,0000,,because if you hang onto the past, you die a little every day.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.25,2:03:12.80,en,,0000,0000,0000,,And for myself,
Dialogue: 0,2:03:13.30,2:03:15.13,en,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'd rather live.


